@* Reconnect Modal - shows when Blazor Server connection is lost.

   Blazor Server needs a constant connection to the server.
   If the connection drops (network issue, server restart), this
   modal appears to let the user know what's happening.

   This is a "static" component - no @code section because
   the JavaScript file handles all the interactivity.
*@

@* Load the JavaScript that handles reconnection logic *@
<script type="module" src="@Assets["Components/Layout/ReconnectModal.razor.js"]"></script>

@*
   HTML <dialog> element for the modal popup.
   id="components-reconnect-modal" is used by Blazor and JavaScript to find this element.
   data-nosnippet tells search engines not to index this content.
   Styling: neo-card, positioned at 20% from top (mt-[20vh]), 20rem wide.
*@
<dialog id="components-reconnect-modal" data-nosnippet class="neo-card mt-[20vh] w-[20rem] p-8">
    <div class="components-reconnect-container text-center">

        @* Loading Animation - spinning dots while reconnecting *@
        <div class="components-rejoining-animation" aria-hidden="true">
            <div></div>
            <div></div>
        </div>

        @* STATE 1: First reconnection attempt in progress *@
        <p class="components-reconnect-first-attempt-visible">
            Rejoining the server...
        </p>

        @* STATE 2: Reconnection failed, will retry automatically *@
        <p class="components-reconnect-repeated-attempt-visible">
            Rejoin failed... trying again in <span id="components-seconds-to-next-attempt"></span> seconds.
        </p>

        @* STATE 3: Reconnection completely failed - show retry button *@
        <p class="components-reconnect-failed-visible">
            Failed to rejoin.<br/>Please retry or reload the page.
        </p>
        <button id="components-reconnect-button" class="components-reconnect-failed-visible neo-button px-6 py-1">
            Retry
        </button>

        @* STATE 4: Session paused by server (maintenance, timeout, etc.) *@
        <p class="components-pause-visible">
            The session has been paused by the server.
        </p>
        <button id="components-resume-button" class="components-pause-visible neo-button px-6 py-1">
            Resume
        </button>

        @* STATE 5: Resume attempt failed completely *@
        <p class="components-resume-failed-visible">
            Failed to resume the session.<br/>Please reload the page.
        </p>
    </div>
</dialog>

@* NOTE: No @code section here. This component is controlled entirely by
   JavaScript (ReconnectModal.razor.js) and Blazor's built-in reconnection logic.
   The CSS classes control which message is visible at each state. *@